snippet.textDisplay: It feels like Coke Studio Bangla has started making anything just for the sake of being different. The recent releases seem to lack the soul and creativity that once defined the show. It’s almost as if they’ve forgotten that the audience does understand good music — we connect to depth, not just experiments. Honestly, quite an unexpected and disappointing direction from Coke Studio Bangla.

snippet.textDisplay: I am a listener of this song more than 25 years. I don’t like the way it has been composed here. Someone should understand the original gloomy composition along with the sad lyrics. As if no one has any proper feeling to understand the lyrics. Singing a sad gloomy song and dancing for sake of coke composition. Musicians are all great. But cooking should not be like this. I had to listen to the original song again to bring back my good feeling. Original one rocks forever.
